The paper discusses the use of massive MIMO for improving wireless capacity in indoor environments, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed approach involves coordination among base stations and distributed interference suppression, which relates to system and control (cs.SY). The paper also evaluates the performance of different schemes for sub-6 GHz deployments, which involves measurements and modeling (cs.MM) and augmented reality (cs.AR) for visualization of the results.
